This paper discusses the management of complex data in decision-support systems, which is a topic that falls under the scope of several computer science sub-categories. The most relevant sub-category is likely cs.DB (Databases), as the paper specifically focuses on data warehousing. The paper also discusses the use of metadata and domain-related knowledge, which are important topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper proposes a solution for integrating knowledge and metadata, which is a topic in software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of an XML framework, which is a common tool in deep learning (cs.DL).
